SUMMARY:Adult Education: Mothers of God
DESCRIPTION:Mothers of God | May 10 | 9:00 a.m. in the library. | led by Ken Kovacs\nBarbara Brown Taylor is a renowned American Episcopal priest and preacher\, acclaimed author\, and educator known for her focus on spirituality\, nature\, and finding sacredness in everyday life. A former parish minister\, she became a prominent teacher of religion at Piedmont College and a New York Times best-selling author of books such as Learning to Walk in the Dark and An Altar in the World. In 1997\, she gave the prestigious Lyman Beecher Lectures on preaching at Yale University\, which was later published as When God is Silent (1997). This Sunday\, discuss her sermon “Mothers of God\,” featured in her book Gospel Medicine (Cowley Publications\, 1995). In this moving piece\, Taylor explores what it means for us to bear Christ into the world today.
URL:https://catonsvillepres.org/event/adult-education-mothers-of-god/
LOCATION:Library
CATEGORIES:Adult Education
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://catonsvillepres.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Bearwalk_CPC_10.18__259.jpg
END:VEVENT
