SUMMARY:Worship (Online and In Person)
DESCRIPTION:Worship with us at 10:30 a.m. in the Sanctuary.\nWorship is at the center of our church life\, the very foundation for our rhythms of service\, mission\, education\, formation\, and fellowship. It is the home we return to\, where we encounter the living God who is breathing and moving throughout our world and lives. You are invited to worship with us: in your faith\, and in your doubt. \nOur expression of worship is rooted in the Reformed tradition and oriented around the scripture. Services are structured in four parts: gathering as the church\, hearing the Word of God\, responding to this good news\, and departing in love and service. These four movements shape our hearts and our minds\, engaging our souls through music\, prayer\, faithful questioning\, and meeting one another in our burdens and triumphs. \nWorship online\nIf you prefer to call in by telephone\, please subscribe to our weekly newsletter. \nBulletins\nThe order of worship and bulletin for each week’s worship service are posted on Friday in that week’s worship event in the calendar. Go to the calendar and find Sunday’s worship to follow along at home. A link to the bulletin is also emailed in our weekly newsletter on Friday. \nSee All Events
URL:https://catonsvillepres.org/event/worship-online-and-in-person-2026-05-10/
LOCATION:Sanctuary
CATEGORIES:Worship
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://catonsvillepres.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Bearwalk_CPC_10.18__524-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
