SUMMARY:Presbyterian Women: Reflections Circle
DESCRIPTION:About Presbyterian Women\nPresbyterian Women is a national organization in the Presbyterian Church (U.S.A.) that draws people together for mutual support\, faith formation\, service\, and public witness. Founded in the mid-1800s\, the predecessor to Presbyterian Women brought women together to fight for social justice\, mend the wounds of the church\, and build a society which is more hospitable\, equitable\, and just. Despite denominational splits\, merges\, and ongoing reformation\, there are over 200\,000 active participants who share these responsibilities and privileges\, laboring with God to nurture and support one another. \nPresbyterian Women at Catonsville Presbyterian Church\nOur church has small groups of women and non-binary people\, called circles\, that meet monthly to follow a Bible study curriculum and enjoy fellowship and support. Each circle sets its own schedule\, location\, and agenda in order to accommodate members’ schedules. \nDue to enthusiastic participation\, there is limited availability for Presbyterian Women. Please contact the church office to learn more. \nMORE ABOUT PRESBYTERIAN WOMEN
URL:https://catonsvillepres.org/event/reflections/2026-05-13/
CATEGORIES:Fellowship and Connection
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://catonsvillepres.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Bearwalk_CPC_10.18__734.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Vickie Lord":MAILTO:lord.victoria@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
