SUMMARY:Contemplative Prayer and Meditation
DESCRIPTION:Contemplative prayer draws our awareness to the deep presence and movement of God in our hearts\, minds\, and bodies—all of who we are. In contemplative prayer\, we spend time listening rather than speaking\, allowing our attention to soften\, quiet\, and move inward. \nEach week during contemplative listening\, members will engage in loosely-guided practices of listening\, prayer\, and meditation. You’re encouraged to make your surroundings peaceful\, restorative\, calming\, by lighting a candle\, sinking into a comfortable chair\, and reducing distractions from your phone or household. Sessions are held on Zoom. \nJOIN MEETING
URL:https://catonsvillepres.org/event/contemplative-prayer-and-meditation-2/2026-05-18/
LOCATION:Zoom Online Meeting
CATEGORIES:Adult Education
